<div class="container-fluid px-0">
    <div class="relative pb-5">
        <div class="background-container bg-home">
            <div class="background curve av-bg-dark" style="z-index: 1;"></div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="container-fluid px-0 bg-home">
    <div class="container-fluid">
        <div class="container mt-5 pt-5">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-lg-8 mx-auto">
                    <div class="text-center">
                        <h2>An experience you'd expect from a commercial framework</h2>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-6 mx-auto text-center">
                    <h4>We have an uncompromising focus on creating a cross-platform UI framework that developers love to build with and businesses trust for their most important apps</h4>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>


    <div class="container">
        <div class="d-flex justify-content-center flex-wrap">
            <div class="card mt-5">
                <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column">
                    <img class="img-fluid mt-3 ms-3" src="~/img/GitHub.svg" width="92" height="92" />
                    <div class="mt-auto ms-3 mb-3">
                        <h6 class="card-title">Open Source</h6>
                        <p class="card-text">Avalonia is open source, free to use and always will be. Clone the source today to dig deeper.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="card mx-md-5 mt-5">
                <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column">
                    <img class="img-fluid mt-3 ms-3" src="~/img/VS.svg" width="92" height="92" />
                    <div class="mt-auto ms-3 mb-3">
                        <h6 class="card-title">Visual Studio Extension</h6>
                        <p class="card-text">The free VS extension provides everything needed to start, including a XAML previewer.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="card mt-5">
                <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column">
                    <img class="img-fluid mt-3 ms-3" src="~/img/jb-colour.svg" width="92" height="92" />
                    <div class="mt-auto ms-3 mb-3">
                        <h6 class="card-title">JetBrains Rider & R#</h6>
                        <p class="card-text">JetBrains deep understanding of Avalonia shines through with rich Rider and R# support.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="d-flex flex-wrap justify-content-center">
            <div class="card mt-5">
                <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column">
                    <div class="container">
                        <div class="row">
                            <div class="col-3">
                                <img src="~/img/windows-brand.svg" />
                            </div>
                            <div class="col-3">
                                <img src="~/img/MacOS_logo.svg" />
                            </div>
                            <div class="col-3">
                                <img src="~/img/linux-brand.svg" />
                            </div>
                            <div class="col-3">
                                <img src="~/img/raspberry-pi-brand.svg" />
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="row mt-3">
                            <div class="col-3">
                                <img src="~/img/WebAssembly_Logo.svg" />
                            </div>
                            <div class="col-3">
                                <img src="~/img/IOS.svg" />
                            </div>
                            <div class="col-3">
                                <img src="~/img/android.svg" />
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="mt-auto ms-3 mb-3">
                        <h6 class="card-title">Cross Platform</h6>
                        <p class="card-text card-caption">Deploy to the platforms you care about with ease.</p>
                        <p class="card-text card-small-print">
                            * Mobile support is in public preview while WASM
                            support
                            is in private preview.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="card mx-md-5 mt-5">
                <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column">
                    <img class="img-fluid mt-3 ms-3" src="~/img/reuse.svg" width="92" height="92" />
                    <div class="mt-auto ms-3 mb-3">
                        <h6 class="card-title">Reuse Existing Skills</h6>
                        <p class="card-text">Leverage existing knowledge, code and packages to kickstart your project.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="card mt-5">
                <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column">
                    <img class="img-fluid mt-3 ms-3" src="~/img/Help.svg" width="92" height="92" />
                    <div class="mt-auto ms-3 mb-3">
                        <h6 class="card-title">Commerical Support</h6>
                        <p class="card-text">Get the support your project needs with one of our commercial support agreements. Help you can count on.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="container mt-5 pt-5">
        <div class="row align-items-center">
            <div class="col-12 col-md">
                <div class="text-left">
                    <h2 class="mb-3">Bring your favourite tools</h2>
                    <h4 class="mb-3"><b>Visual Studio.</b> If you love to develop in Visual Studio, then you’re in luck! The <a href="https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=AvaloniaTeam.AvaloniaforVisualStudio">Avalonia Extension</a> provides XAML IntelliSense and a XAML built-in previewer</h4>
                    <h4 class="mb-3">
                        <b>JetBrains Rider & R#.</b> Offering the deepest understanding of Avalonia,
                        and <a href="https://blog.jetbrains.com/dotnet/2021/04/12/improvements-for-resharper-rider-avalonia/">extensive integration</a> with thier tools, JetBrains delivers huge productivity
                        gains for Avalonia developers.
                    </h4>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="d-lg-block col">
                <img class="img-fluid float-end" src="~/img/rider-ide-screenshot.png" />
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="row align-items-center mt-5 ">
            <div class="col-12 col-md order-md-1">
                <div class="text-left">
                    <h2 class="mb-3">A proven path for WPF app modernization</h2>
                    <h4 class="mb-3"><b>Familiar.</b> Considered a spiritual successor to WPF, Avalonia provides a familiar developer experience allowing you to leverage years of pre-existing knowledge and investments.</h4>
                    <h4 class="mb-3"><b>Proven.</b> Trusted by <b>JetBrains</b> as the best framework for modernising their WPF based tools, used by >170,000 companies, including 431 on the Fortune 500 list.</h4>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="d-lg-block col order-md-0 m-md-5">
                <img class="img-fluid float-start" src="~/img/dotmem.png" />
            </div>
        </div>
       
    </div>
</div>

<div class="container mt-5 pt-5">
    <div class="row justify-content-center">
        <div class="col-12 col-lg-6">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="text-left">
                    <h2 class="mb-3">Join a growing community</h2>
                    <h4 class="mb-3">We’ve seen enormous growth in our developer community as Avalonia has grown in popularity. Join us and be welcomed into our supportive and vibrant community.</h4>
